Cognitive Work Plane (CWP)
1. Purpose of This Document
This document defines the authoritative data model for the Cognitive Work Plane (CWP).
It specifies:
  canonical entities and relationships
  primary identifiers and versioning semantics
  immutability and append-only guarantees
  event sourcing and projection strategy
The model is optimized for agentic supervision, auditability, and replay.
2. Core Modeling Principles
 Definitions are Versioned — work definitions evolve via new versions
 Execution is Event-Sourced — runtime state is derived, never mutated
 Decisions are Append-Only — every decision is preserved
 Assignments are Attributed — actor + reason always recorded
 Cross-Engine References are Immutable — no foreign mutation
3. Authoritative Stores
Primary Store (MVP): PostgreSQL
Supporting Stores (optional):
  Kafka — work and supervision events
  Redis — hot projections
  MongoDB — operator notes and rich annotations
The event ledger is the source of truth for rebuilds.
